items.name: PUSH
desc: requires the button to act like a common push button, means no special action is triggered.

items.name: RESET
desc: When the button is clicked, it performs a reset on its containing form.

items.name: SUBMIT
desc: When the button is clicked, it performs a submit on its containing form.

items.name: URL
desc: When the button is clicked, a URL set for the button is opened.
Specifies to use \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" as submit encoding.
Usually used if the FormSubmitMethod attribute has the value POST.
